-- European Stocks Drop After U.S. Durable Goods Orders Unexpectedly Decline
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-07-28T12:36:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/european-stocks-drop-after-u-s-durable-goods-orders-unexpectedly-decline.html

          
          
             European stocks declined after a
report showed orders for U.S. durable goods unexpectedly fell in
June, adding to evidence the economic recovery is slowing.  
 The Stoxx Europe 600 Index dropped 0.2 percent to 257.54 at
1:35 p.m. in London, having earlier risen as much as 0.6
percent.  
          
          


  


        